<secondary>signals</secondary></indexterm>
<para>This class can receive signals and events. When a signal or event is received a
method of the class is invoked. The name of this method corresponds to the name of the
signal or event. By default all of the signals have a method predefined in the class
to receive the signal. This method performs no actions by default.</para>
<para>In order for the signals to be processed by the user's code you must subclass this
class and override the signal method. You can supply any action you wish to process the
signal.</para>
<para>By default, none of the signals for this class are connected so even if you provide
an override method the method will not be invoked unless the signal is connected first. To
connect a signal you must invoke the <emphasis role="italic">signal_connect</emphasis>
method and provide the name of the signal to be connected.</para>
